# Marketing Manager Portfolio — Personal Safety & Security (Sample Work)

This repo contains **portfolio-style samples** aligned with a Marketing Manager role for a personal safety / security brand.

---

## Campaign: “Everyday Safety, Real Peace of Mind” (4 Weeks)

### Goal
Increase awareness + drive qualified traffic and repeat touchpoints through influencer-led content.

### Primary KPIs
CTR, CAC, CVR, ROAS, Email sign-ups, Affiliate revenue, Engagement rate.

### Target Audiences (Segments)
1) Women commuting / urban lifestyle  
2) Students (campus + night commuting)  
3) Parents / caregivers (peace of mind)  
4) Travelers / hotel stays

### Core Message Pillars
- **Peace of mind** (confidence in daily routines)
- **Simple to carry / easy to use**
- **Everyday scenarios** (commute, parking, running errands, travel)
- **Community + empowerment** (protect yourself, support others)

---

## Content Plan (Weekly Rhythm)
**Weekly output:**
- 4–6 short-form videos (TikTok/IG Reels/YT Shorts)
- Daily stories (polls, Q&A, behind-the-scenes)
- 2 community posts (education + UGC highlights)
- 1 newsletter/week + 2 lifecycle emails/week

### 10 Short-Form Video Concepts (UGC-friendly)
1) “What’s in my bag” + safety item reveal (quick demo)  
2) “Night commute routine” (before/after confidence framing)  
3) “Travel checklist” (hotel/airport scenarios)  
4) “Student campus essentials” (day-in-the-life)  
5) “3 safety habits I use every week” (education-first)  
6) “Gift idea that shows you care” (family/partner angle)  
7) “The moment I realized I needed this” (storytelling hook)  
8) “My mom made me carry this” (humor + relatable)  
9) “Emergency drill: how fast can you access it?” (speed + simplicity)  
10) “Community Q&A” (answer top questions + objections)

### 15 Hook Bank (First 2 seconds)
- “I never used to think about safety… until this happened.”
- “If you commute alone, watch this.”
- “This is the one item I won’t leave home without.”
- “A gift that says ‘I want you safe’.”
- “Here’s how I feel more confident walking to my car.”
- “Students: put this on your checklist.”
- “Travelers: add this to your carry-on.”
- “This takes 2 seconds to access.”
- “My simplest peace-of-mind upgrade.”
- “I used to forget safety—now it’s automatic.”
- “If you’re a parent, this matters.”
- “3 habits that make me feel safer daily.”
- “I wish someone told me this sooner.”
- “This is what I keep by my door.”
- “Quick demo: why it’s so easy to carry.”

### 10 Caption Templates (IG/TikTok)
1) Confidence > fear. Everyday peace of mind. ✅  
2) Small tool, big comfort. Link in bio.  
3) If you commute alone: save this for later.  
4) Students + travelers: this is for you.  
5) A gift that actually matters.  
6) Simple, portable, ready when you are.  
7) Questions? Drop them below — I’ll answer.  
8) Tag someone you care about.  
9) Safety doesn’t have to be complicated.  
10) Real life > perfect life. Be prepared.

---

## Influencer Outreach System

### Ideal Creator Profiles
- Women’s lifestyle, self-care, urban living
- College/student creators
- Parenting / family creators
- Travel creators
- Community educators (tips, routines)

### Selection Criteria
Audience fit, engagement rate, comment quality, content consistency, brand-safe tone, UGC potential.

### Outreach DM (Short)
Hi [Name] — I’m Camila from [Brand]. I loved your video about [specific post].  
We’re launching a safety-focused campaign and would love to collaborate on a short UGC-style video featuring our personal safety device.  
Would you be open to a quick brief? We can offer [paid rate / gifted + commission] + clear creative guidance.

### Outreach Email (Longer)
Subject: Collaboration opportunity — safety-focused UGC for [Brand]

Hi [Name],  
I’m Camila from [Brand]. I’m reaching out because your content on [topic] is a great fit for our audience. We’re building a creator program centered on everyday peace of mind and practical safety routines.  

We’d love to partner with you on:
- 1 short-form UGC video (15–30s) + 3 story frames
- Optional: whitelisting for paid amplification (with your approval)

Compensation: [paid rate] + product (or affiliate commission).  
If you’re interested, I can send a one-page brief with angles and examples.

Best,  
Camila

### Follow-Up Sequence
- D+2: “Just bumping this—happy to send the brief.”
- D+5: Share 2 creative angles + example scripts.
- D+10: Final touch + “open to future collabs”.

---

## Email & SMS Samples (Retention)

### Newsletter (Education + Soft Sell)
Subject: A small habit for everyday peace of mind  
Preview: Simple routines that help you feel more confident, anywhere.

Body:
- 2–3 practical safety habits (education-first)
- “What we use” section (product mention)
- CTA: Shop / Learn more

### Abandoned Cart Email
Subject A: Still thinking it over?  
Subject B: Your peace of mind is waiting

Body:
- Reminder + 1 key benefit
- Social proof snippet (UGC-style line)
- CTA: Complete your order

### SMS (Examples)
- “Quick reminder: your cart is saved. Want to finish checkout? [link]”
- “New drop: everyday safety essentials are back in stock. [link]”
- “Free shipping ends tonight—grab peace of mind before it’s gone. [link]”

---

## Reporting & Optimization Playbook

### Weekly Dashboard
Reach, Engagement rate, Video watch time, CTR, CPC, CAC, CVR, ROAS, Email capture rate, Affiliate revenue.

### Decision Rules
- Low CTR → test stronger hooks, clearer benefit, tighter CTA
- High CTR / low CVR → align landing page message + add trust elements
- Strong creator → scale via whitelisting / paid amplification
- Weak segment → adjust offer framing + personalize messaging

---

## Tools
Canva, Google Docs, Slack, Asana + any analytics/CRM stack provided (Meta, TikTok, GA4, Klaviyo).
